etpack-related-posts":[{"id":29330,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/05\/13\/sahabah-said-when-praised\/","url_meta":{"origin":31749,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Humility: What the companions said when praised","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 13, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"\u2018Adi ibn Artah reported: When a man among the companions of the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, was praised for his righteousness, he would say, \u201cO Allah, do not blame me for what they say and forgive me for what they do not know!\u201d Source: al-Adab al-Mufrad lil-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":8209,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/10\/15\/why-servants-despair\/","url_meta":{"origin":31749,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Laughter: Why make My servants despair?","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 15, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, came out to a group of his companions while they were laughing and talking. The Prophet said, \u201cBy the One in whose hand is my soul, if you knew what I knew, you would laugh little and weep often.\u201d\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":8039,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/10\/13\/bad-neighbors-yawm-al-qiyamah\/","url_meta":{"origin":31749,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Neighbors: How many bad neighbors on Judgment Day?","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 13, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Umar reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cHow many neighbors will be brought with their neighbors on the Day of Resurrection? One will say: O Lord, this man closed his door to me and refused to show courtesy!\u201d Source: al-Adab al-Mufrad lil-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 111\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":8747,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/10\/24\/ibn-sireen-entertainment-sahabah\/","url_meta":{"origin":31749,"position":3},"title":"Ibn Sirin on Fun: Companions would have fun, sing poetry","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 24, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Qurrah ibn Khalid reported: I asked Muhammad ibn Sirin, may Allah have mercy on him, \u201cDid the companions have fun?\u201d Ibn Sirin said, \u201cThey were not but people. Ibn Umar, may Allah be pleased with him, would have fun and compose songs of poetry.\u201d Source: H\u0323ilyat al-Awliya\u0304' 2437 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0642\u064f\u0631\u064e\u0651\u0629\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":110,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2010\/11\/13\/not-allowed-prank-scare\/","url_meta":{"origin":31749,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Pranks: Not allowed to scare another Muslim on purpose","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 13, 2010","for